{
  "texts": [
    "For four classes, the average accuracy was high again at 95.50%, while the three classes gave us an average of 76.60%.",
    "Finally, we examined the \"whole image\" method with the same 80-20 data split.",
    "A four-class grouping resulted in an average accuracy of 78.34%.",
    "One group of three classes managed a much higher average accuracy of 89.86%, while the other three-class group had an average accuracy of 78.22%.",
    "Overall, these results show that the different methods and the number of classes used can have varied impacts on performance."
  ]
}